\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Marcus spent the next few hours navigating the forest and dealing with the more aggressive beasts he encountered. His imbued Mana spikes and imbued barriers were every bit the improvement he had hoped they would be, allowing him to handle a few groups of lower level beasts with ease as well as a single, stronger creature that he encountered at the  base of a large hill. A hill that held a cave with a very strong mana signature deep within it. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He spent several minutes studying the mouth of the cave and the ground before it, looking for the tracks of any animals that might call it home. Finding no tracks actually entering the cave, he carefully made his way inside. After a couple steps, Marcus realized this was no natural cave. It wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t apparent from the overgrown outside, but the entryway was a carved stone archway engraved with magical formations to deter animals from entering. The walls were smooth flat stone blocks that had once been sheathed in pristine white plaster that was now broken and crumbling. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 At the back of the deep entryway, a spiral stone staircase descended into the ground. His Mana senses insisted that was where he would find the Mana signature he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d been following. So he began his descent, carefully edging into the growing darkness. As he finished the first full turn of the spiral he should have been plunged into complete blackness, instead a series of small crystals set into the wall at waist height flickered to life and began radiating a soft blue-white radiance to illuminate the area. He continued his cautious descent, testing each stair with the end of his staff before stepping down onto it. It took a total of seven turns of the spiral to reach the bottom of the stairs, which ended in a black corridor some five meters wide with a vaulted ceiling. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 When he crossed the threshold of the corridor, torches set in sconces at intervals along the walls burst to life with an eerie bluish-green flame that gave off light without heat or smoke. At the far end of the hall, some 50 meters ahead, the corridor was sealed by a pair of large, intricately carved stone doors. As Marcus stopped and examined the engravings, his Lingual Savant ability activated and he could suddenly read the words carved into the lintel of the doorway.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\i0 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93In Discovery we find Truth. In Truth we find Freedom.\u8221\'94 }
